# Documentation

## Single source of truth

All architecture and operator docs live in committed repo files:

- **Documentation entry:** [`docs/README.md`](docs/README.md) (pipeline architecture; edit first for repo/CI changes)
- **Operator commands:** [`docs/usage.md`](docs/usage.md) (GitHub and local copy-paste runs)
- **mirror-init:** [`docs/mirror-init.md`](docs/mirror-init.md) ([Tooling branch layout](docs/mirror-init.md#tooling-branch-layout))
- **mirror-poll:** [`docs/mirror-poll.md`](docs/mirror-poll.md)
- **mirror-sync:** [`docs/mirror-sync.md`](docs/mirror-sync.md) (CI on mirror repos)
- **mirror-merge:** [`docs/mirror-merge.md`](docs/mirror-merge.md) (replay algorithm)

Edit the doc that matches the area you are changing. Do not create other parallel
design files unless the user explicitly asks.

## Do not use Cursor internal plans

Do **not** treat Cursor's internal plan feature as the project design:

- No authoring or updating `~/.cursor/plans/*.plan.md` as the canonical design
- No copying design notes to/from Cursor-only paths instead of the repo
- No "save to repo later" -- changes belong in `docs/` in the same turn

## When docs change

1. Update [`docs/README.md`](docs/README.md) when pipeline map, repos, CI boundaries, or operator flows change
2. Update the matching stage doc for stage-specific detail
3. Update [`docs/usage.md`](docs/usage.md) when copy-paste operator commands change
4. Commit doc changes when the user asks (or as part of an agreed docs pass)
5. Reference these paths in code, rules, and PRs -- not Cursor plan URLs

## Agent behavior

- Read design from committed docs, not from conversation-only or Cursor-internal state
- Start from [`docs/README.md`](docs/README.md) for pipeline architecture
- Operator commands: [`usage.md`](docs/usage.md); stage detail: `mirror-init.md`, `mirror-poll.md`, `mirror-sync.md`, `mirror-merge.md`
- If committed docs and chat history disagree, the committed files win unless the user is actively revising them
